g|150px|openPlaG graphs screenshot]]|| GUI || GPL || {{yes}} ||{{dts|2018|06|12}} / 3.5 || Any (PHP 5) || graph plotter\n|-\n| [[Orange (software)|Orange]]||[[File:Paint Data - example workflow.png|150px|Orange example workflow screenshot]]|| GUI, Python scripting|| GPL || {{yes}} ||{{dts|2017|09|03}} / 3.5 || GNU/Linux, Windows, Mac OS X || A visual programming data-flow software suite with widgets for statistical [[data analysis]], interactive [[data visualization]], [[data mining]], and [[machine learning]].\n|-\n|[[Origin (data analysis software)|Origin]]||  || GUI, COM, C/{{nowrap|C++}} and scripting|| proprietary || {{no}} || {{dts|2017|06|22}} / 2017 SR2 || Windows || Multi-layer 2D, 3D and statistical graphs for science and engineering. Built-in digitizing tool. Auto-recalculation and reporting. Programmable, with access to [[NAG Numerical Library]].\n|-\n| [[ParaView]]||  || GUI, Python scripting|| GPL || {{Yes}} || {{dts|2018|06|19}} / 5.5.2 || Linux/Unix, {{nowrap|Mac OS X}}, Windows || Parallel scientific and [[Computational Fluid Dynamics]] visualizations\n|-\n| [[Perl Data Language|PDL]]||[[File:Pdl-plot.png|150px|PDL]]||  || Artistic License / GPL || {{Yes}} || {{dts|2018|05|06}} / 2.019 || Perl Data Language ||\n|-\n|[[PGPLOT]]||  || FORTRAN, C ||  || {{no}} || {{dts|2001|02|26}} / 5.2.2 || Linux, Mac, Windows || (Fortran) California Institute of Technology, Inactive {{as of|2001|lc=y}}\n|-\n| [[ploticus]]||[[File:Ploticus wikipedia stats.png|150px|A plot of Wikipedia statistics in Ploticus]]|| Command line, C || GPL || {{yes}} || {{dts|2013|05}} / 2.42 || Linux, Mac, Windows || plots and charts from data\n|-\n|[[Plotly]]||[[File:Plotly screenshot.png|150px|A plot made using plotly]]||[[GUI]], [[command line]] [[Python (programming language)|Python]]|| Commercial || {{no}} ||  || Any (web-based) || plots and charts in browser, web-sharing and exporting, drag-and-drop data import, Python command line\n|-\n| [[plotutils]]||  ||[[command line]], C/{{nowrap|C++}}|| GPL || {{yes}} || {{dts|2009|09|27}} / 2.6 || Linux, Mac, Windows || Collection of command line programs, C/C++ API\n|-\n| [[PLplot]]||[[File:Plplot.png|150px|3D surface plot]]|| Ada, C/{{nowrap|C++}}/D, Fortran 77/90, C, {{nowrap|C++}}, Java, Lisp, Lua, OCaml, Octave, Perl, Python, Tcl/Tk || LGPL || {{yes}} || {{dts|2017|08|26}} / 5.13.0|| Linux, Mac, Windows || Many different output formats: CGM, GIF, Jpeg, Png, Latex, PBM, PDF, Postscript, SVG, XFig, Qt, wxWidgets\n|-\n| [[PSPP]]||<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:pspp-ex1.png|150px|PSPP example]]  -->||[[GUI]], [[command line]]||[[GPL]]|| {{yes}} || {{dts|2017|08|20}} / 1.0.0 || Linux, Mac, Windows || Statistical analysis of sampled data. Free replacement for [[SPSS]].\n|-\n| [[QtiPlot]]||  || GUI, Python || proprietary || {{no}} || {{dts|2017|05|31}} / 0.9.9.11 || Linux, Mac, Windows || Python scriptable\n|-\n|[[R (programming language)|R]]||[[File:Plots from lm example.svg|150px]]||[[R (programming language)#Graphical user interfaces|Third party]]||[[GPL]]|| {{yes}} || {{dts|2018|07|02}} / 3.5.1(\"Feather Spray\") || Linux, Mac, Windows || In addition to base graphics, has a large number of graphics packages including ''lattice'' and ''[[ggplot2]]''.<ref>https://cran.r-project.org/web/views/Graphics.html</ref> Interoperabile with other free software packages.\n|-\n| [[ROOT]]||[[File:2D ROI.jpg|150px|ROOT plot showing regions of interest in a 2D distribution]]|| GUI, {{nowrap|C++}}, Python, Ruby|| LGPL || {{yes}} || {{dts|2018|08|23}} / 6.14.04 || Linux, Mac, Windows || De facto standard in high energy physics\n|-\n| [[RRDtool]]||[[File:Rrddemo.png|150px|RRDtool]]|| Command line || GPL || {{Yes}} || {{dts|2017|05|17}} / 1.7.0 || Linux, Windows ||\n|-\n|[[S-PLUS]]||  ||  || Proprietary || {{No}} || {{dts|2010|11}} / 8.2 ||  || Statistics\n|-\n|[[S (programming language)|S]]||  ||  ||  ||  ||  ||  || Statistics\n|-\n| [[SAS System]]||  ||  || Proprietary || {{No}} || {{dts|2013|07|10}} / 9.4 ||  || S